● All tasks complete. Here's a summary:                                                                                                                                                                                                           Glass app (glass-bike-hud) - Built and installed on Glass                                                               - BikeHudActivity.java — HUD with HR as 72sp hero metric (color-coded by zone), speed, distance, elapsed time           - BleManager.java — BLE client adapted from vesc-glass with same scan/auto-connect/trusted device patterns, but         receive-only (no polling)                                                                                               - BikeData.java — data model with mph/miles conversion helpers                                                          - Custom GATT service UUID 0000ff10 with 3 characteristics (HR, Location, Trip)                                                                                                                                                                 Watch app (watch-bike-hud) - Built, ready to install on Galaxy Watch                                                    - BikeSensorService.kt — foreground service reading HR sensor + GPS, pushes via BLE GATT notifications                  - BleGattServer.kt — GATT peripheral advertising custom service with 3 notify characteristics                           - DistanceTracker.kt — GPS distance accumulation with jitter/accuracy filtering                                         - WatchBikeActivity.kt — simple start/stop UI showing current HR, GPS status, BLE connections, distance, elapsed time                                                                                                                           APK locations:   - Glass: /home/stathis/glass-apps/glass-bike-hud/app/build/outputs/apk/debug/app-debug.apk (installed)                  - Watch: /home/stathis/glass-apps/watch-bike-hud/app/build/outputs/apk/debug/app-debug.apk (ready to install when       watch is connected via ADB)                                                                                                                                                                                                                   ✻ Sautéed for 19m 35s                                                                                                       ❯ the watch only has the magnetic charging cable. how do you connect adb to galaxy s 4?                                                                                                                           ● ADB over WiFi — the Galaxy Watch 4 supports wireless debugging.                                                                                                                                                                                 On the watch:                                                                                                                                                                        1. Settings > About watch > Software information — tap "Software version" 5 times to enable Developer options           2. Settings > Developer options — enable ADB debugging and Debug over Wi-Fi                                             3. It will show an IP:port like 192.168.1.50:5555   On your PC:   adb connect 192.168.1.50:5555   adb -s 192.168.1.50:5555 install -r /home/stathis/glass-apps/watch-bike-hud/app/build/outputs/apk/debug/app-debug.apk   The watch and PC need to be on the same WiFi network. On newer Wear OS versions (3.5+), it may use Wireless debugging    instead, which requires a pairing step first:   1. Developer options > Wireless debugging — enable and tap to enter   2. Tap Pair new device — shows a pairing code and port   3. adb pair 192.168.1.50:<pairing-port> — enter the code   4. Then adb connect 192.168.1.50:<debug-port> (the port shown on the main wireless debugging screen, not the pairing   port) 

