                                                                                                                                                                                 ✻ Sautéed for 19m 35s                                                                                                       ❯ the watch only has the magnetic charging cable. how do you connect adb to galaxy s 4?                                                                                                                           ● ADB over WiFi — the Galaxy Watch 4 supports wireless debugging.                                                                                                                                                                                 On the watch:                                                                                                                                                                        1. Settings > About watch > Software information — tap "Software version" 5 times to enable Developer options           2. Settings > Developer options — enable ADB debugging and Debug over Wi-Fi                                             3. It will show an IP:port like 192.168.1.50:5555   On your PC:   adb connect 192.168.1.50:5555   adb -s 192.168.1.50:5555 install -r /home/stathis/glass-apps/watch-bike-hud/app/build/outputs/apk/debug/app-debug.apk   The watch and PC need to be on the same WiFi network. On newer Wear OS versions (3.5+), it may use Wireless debugging    instead, which requires a pairing step first:   1. Developer options > Wireless debugging — enable and tap to enter   2. Tap Pair new device — shows a pairing code and port   3. adb pair 192.168.1.50:<pairing-port> — enter the code   4. Then adb connect 192.168.1.50:<debug-port> (the port shown on the main wireless debugging screen, not the pairing   port) 
